lead_paragraph: Seattle Storm forward Lauren Jackson won the second Most Valuable Player award of her W.N.B.A career. Jackson, who also won in 2003, led the league in scoring for the third time with a career-best 23.8 points a game and also led the W.N.B.A. with 9.7 rebounds a game.
